        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e9bcb4/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-01-02T03:47:05.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Dessus is, indeed, upslope from Dessous, which is considered the favored sector.  Why, I don\u2019t know for sure, other than perhaps vineyards at that elevation throughout the Cote d\u2019Or generally don\u2019t produce wines of the same character and distinction as those located in the tenderloin just below.  Benjamin Leroux makes a Vireuils Dessus.</p>",
